25|$|The 2010 Buick LaCrosse CXS is {{the first}} North American car to {{incorporate}} a front suspension design, marketed as HiPer Strut, designed to improve ride and handling and reduces <b>torque</b> <b>steer.</b> The Buick LaCrosse CXS includes a system marketed as Real Time Damping that adjusts the damping forces of the shocks and struts for improved ride and handling.|$|E
