5000|$|Equalise {{the torque}} better between the driveshafts {{by using a}} low {{friction}} differential. The torque difference is zero if the differential is frictionless, and limited slip differentials, intended to increase power transfer, actually make <b>torque</b> <b>steer</b> much worse. For this reason, limited slip differentials by automobile transmission manufacturers like Quaife, Torsen, TrueTrac, Gold Trac have not been much used until recently, and require other measures to be implemented, such as careful positioning of suspension pivot points and driveshaft CV joints, {{in order to keep}} the resultant <b>torque</b> <b>steer</b> to a manageable amount. Limited slip differentials do not improve cornering, or steering feel, however they will improve power transfer in situations where one wheel experiences limited adhesion, and so may improve overall performance.|$|E
